2.3 Tidy Data Construction: 
The core rule: one row = one trip observation = one choice occasion. The columns must include:
* person_id, city, chosen_mode
* tt_bus, tt_metro, tt_car, tt_bike — travel times for all alternatives (including unchosen)
* cost_bus, cost_metro, cost_car, cost_bike — generalised costs for all alternatives
* acc_bus, acc_metro, acc_car, acc_bike — access times for all alternatives
* wait_bus, wait_metro — waiting times (PT modes only)
* income_group, car_available, trip_distance_km, departure_hour
2.4 Data Cleaning - Follow a treatment rule to remove wrong entries from unusual realities:
* Travel times > 180 minutes for a commute: flag, investigate, likely remove
* Zero travel time: data error,so remove it
* Missing cost: impute using mode-specific average per city, log the imputation
* Implausible access time (> 60 minutes walk to a bus stop): flag, keep but annotate
